   241	It is interesting that such a fundamental notion as channel capacity has
   242	no thermodynamic analog. In thermodynamics the absolute value of the
   243	entropy has no meaning; only entropy differences can be measured in
   244	experiments. Consequently the condition that $H$ is maximized,
   245	equivalent to the statement that the Helmholz free energy function
   246	vanishes ($A = E - TS = 0$), corresponds to no condition which could be
   247	detected experimentally.
   248	
   249	Generalization of the above analysis to the case where the different
   250	words are no longer statistically independent is also straightforward,
   251	and corresponds to the transition in statistical mechanics from the
   252	Maxwell-Boltzman \"molecular\" viewpoint, to the Gibbsian \"global\"
   253	viewpoint. We mention two examples of the correspondence which then
   254	exists.
   255	
